The route builder now has a complete undo system and much more intuitive waypoint management! ­¤öä­¤Śæ’ĖÅŌ£©

## Task: Fix Mobile AppBar Layout Overflow

### Issue:

User reported that on mobile devices, the AppBar controls were overflowing at the top, causing layout issues. The buttons from "Reverse" to "Map Type" needed to be put on a second line for iPhone screens while keeping the single-line layout for iPad/tablet and desktop.

### Problem Identified:

**Mobile Layout Overflow**: The AppBar was using a single-row flexbox layout that caused buttons to overflow on small screens, making the interface unusable on mobile devices.

### Solution Applied:

**Responsive AppBar Layout**:

```tsx
// Before: Single line layout (caused mobile overflow)
<div className="flex items-center gap-2 p-2">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 flex-1 min-w-0">
    {/* Route name */}
  </div>
  <div className="flex items-center gap-1">
    {/* All buttons in one row */}
  </div>
</div>

// After: Responsive stacked layout
<div className="flex flex-col gap-2 p-2 md:flex-row md:items-center">
  {/* Route name row - always full width */}
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2 flex-1 min-w-0">
    {/* Route name */}
  </div>

  {/* Action buttons row - wrap on mobile, single line on desktop */}
  <div className="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1 md:flex-nowrap">
    {/* All buttons with responsive wrapping */}
  </div>
</div>
```

### Results:

