**Lesson Learned**: Sometimes the simplest solution is the best. The location button was working before, but adding complex debugging, loading states, and permission checks actually broke the functionality. Reverted to the basic, proven implementation.

**14. Ō£ģ iOS-Aware Geolocation Solution**:

```tsx
// iOS feature detect
const isIOS =
  /iPad|iPhone|iPod/.test(navigator.userAgent) ||
  (navigator.platform === "MacIntel" && navigator.maxTouchPoints > 1);

// Single, resilient entry point for location
const getDeviceLocation = (): Promise<GeolocationPosition> => {
  if (!("geolocation" in navigator)) {
    return Promise.reject(
      new Error("Geolocation is not available on this device.")
    );
  }
  if (!isSecureContext) {
    return Promise.reject(
      new Error("Location requires HTTPS. Open this page over https://")
    );
  }

  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    let resolved = false;
    let watchId: number | null = null;

    const cleanup = () => {
      if (watchId !== null) {
        navigator.geolocation.clearWatch(watchId);
        watchId = null;
      }
    };

    // iOS sometimes only returns quickly via watchPosition
    // Start a watch that will resolve on the first fix.
    watchId = navigator.geolocation.watchPosition(
      (pos) => {
        if (resolved) return;
        resolved = true;
        cleanup();
        resolve(pos);
      },
      (err) => {
        console.warn("watchPosition error:", err);
      },
      {
        enableHighAccuracy: true,
        maximumAge: 0,
        timeout: 15000,
      }
    );

    // In parallel, try a quick getCurrentPosition (often enough on desktop)
    navigator.geolocation.getCurrentPosition(
      (pos) => {
        if (resolved) return;
        resolved = true;
        cleanup();
        resolve(pos);
      },
      (err) => {
        console.warn("getCurrentPosition error:", err);
        // Only reject if the watch hasn't produced anything after a grace period
        setTimeout(() => {
          if (!resolved) {
            cleanup();
            reject(err);
          }
        }, 16000); // give watchPosition time to produce a fix
      },
      {
        enableHighAccuracy: true,
        maximumAge: 0,
        timeout: 8000,
      }
    );
  });
};

// Enhanced addCurrentLocation with iOS-specific error handling
const addCurrentLocation = async () => {
  try {
    // Show loading state for iOS devices that might take longer
    if (isIOS) {
      setIsSearching(true);
    }

    const pos = await getDeviceLocation();
    const coords = { lat: pos.coords.latitude, lng: pos.coords.longitude };
    map.current?.setCenter(coords);
    map.current?.setZoom(16);
    setPendingCoord(coords);
    setShowAddHereToast(true);
  } catch (err: any) {
    console.warn("Geolocation failed:", err);
    // Friendly, actionable iOS guidance
    let msg = "Unable to get your location.";
    if (err?.code === 1 /* PERMISSION_DENIED */) {
      msg =
        "Location permission is blocked. On iPhone/iPad: Settings ŌåÆ Privacy & Security ŌåÆ Location Services ŌåÆ Safari Websites ŌåÆ Allow While Using & enable Precise Location. Then reload the page.";
    } else if (!isSecureContext) {
      msg = "Location requires HTTPS. Open this page over https:// and retry.";
    } else if (isIOS) {
      msg =
        "iOS couldn't get a fix. Make sure Location Services are ON and Precise Location is enabled for Safari Websites, then try again.";
    }
    setErrorMessage(msg);
    setTimeout(() => setErrorMessage(null), 8000);
  } finally {
    // Always clear loading state
    setIsSearching(false);
  }
};
```

**iOS-Specific Features**:

- **Dual Strategy**: Uses both `watchPosition` and `getCurrentPosition` for iOS cold-start reliability
- **Extended Timeouts**: 15s for watch, 8s for getCurrentPosition with 16s grace period
- **Permission Guidance**: Clear iOS-specific instructions for Settings ŌåÆ Privacy & Security
- **HTTPS Check**: Verifies secure context required for iOS geolocation
- **Loading States**: Visual feedback during longer iOS GPS fixes
- **Error Messages**: Actionable guidance for common iOS location issues

**15. Ō£ģ Fixed iOS Safari Address Bar Background Shrinking**:

**Root Cause Identified**: iOS Safari address bar tucking away during scroll causes viewport height changes, making the background appear to shrink.

**Clean CSS Fix Applied**:

```css
/* iOS Safari address bar fix - prevents background shrinking when address bar tucks away */
@supports (-webkit-touch-callout: none) {
  .h-\[100dvh\] {
    height: -webkit-fill-available;
    min-height: -webkit-fill-available;
  }
}
```

**What This Fixes**:

- **Address Bar Behavior**: Handles iOS Safari address bar show/hide during scroll
- **Stable Background**: Prevents background shrinking when viewport height changes
- **Minimal Impact**: Only affects iOS devices, no unnecessary CSS properties
- **Clean Solution**: Uses Tailwind's `h-[100dvh]` class with iOS-specific override

**16. Ō£ģ Fixed Auto-Search While Typing Issue**:

**Problem Identified**: Search function was automatically moving the map to search results while users were still typing, creating a poor user experience.

**Root Cause**: `useEffect` hook with `debouncedSearchValue` was triggering searches automatically after 350ms of typing inactivity.

**Solution Applied**:

- **Removed Auto-Search**: Eliminated the `useEffect` that triggered on `debouncedSearchValue` changes
- **Manual Search Only**: Search now only triggers when user clicks search button or presses Enter
- **Cleaned Up Code**: Removed unused `useDebounce` hook and `debouncedSearchValue` state
- **Better UX**: Users can now type their complete search without the map jumping around

**User Experience Benefits**:

- Ō£ģ **No More Map Jumping**: Map stays stable while typing
- Ō£ģ **User Control**: Search only happens when explicitly requested
- Ō£ģ **Cleaner Interface**: No unexpected behavior during input
- Ō£ģ **Professional Feel**: Matches user expectations for search functionality

